Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.junit.provider

Interface ExtensionContextBasedProvider<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type provided by the method
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CharacterizationAlgorithmFactoryProvider, ConfigurationProvider, ConverterProvider, GeneratorProvider, ModelProvider, ReporterProvider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DelegatingConfigurationProvider, MethodBasedProvider
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ExtensionContextBasedProvider<T>
    A general interface used to mark a provider for a resource. They are most likely used together with source definitions form annotations. For example, ModelFromMethod defines the name of a method from which a InputParameterModel is loaded and MethodBasedProvider then loads the model from this method.
